video.title: The Crown
video.synopsis: This drama follows the political rivalries and romance of Queen Elizabeth II's reign and the events that shaped the second half of the 20th century.

episodes.synopsis: A young Princess Elizabeth marries Prince Philip. As King George VI’s health worsens, Winston Churchill is elected prime minister for the second time.
episodes.title: Wolferton Splash

episodes.synopsis: With King George too ill to travel, Elizabeth and Philip embark on a four-continent Commonwealth tour. Party leaders attempt to undermine Churchill.
episodes.title: Hyde Park Corner

episodes.synopsis: With Elizabeth in a new role, Philip tries to assert some power. Churchill wants to delay the coronation. King George’s disgraced brother arrives.
episodes.title: Windsor

episodes.synopsis: When dense smog cripples London for days and creates a serious health hazard, Churchill’s inaction leaves him vulnerable to his political enemies.
episodes.title: Act of God

episodes.synopsis: Elizabeth rejects protocol by appointing Philip to coordinate her coronation, but his ideas create conflict. The Duke of Windsor returns to London.
episodes.title: Smoke and Mirrors

episodes.synopsis: Margaret and Peter come to Elizabeth with a request. With a royal scandal about to break in the newspapers, the Queen Mother intervenes.
episodes.title: Gelignite

episodes.synopsis: As the Soviets test the H-bomb, both Churchill and Eden have major health crises. Angry about her inadequate education, Elizabeth hires a tutor.
episodes.title: Scientia Potentia Est

episodes.synopsis: Elizabeth and Philip go on an exhausting world journey. Margaret takes over some of her sister’s official duties and tries to liven things up.
episodes.title: Pride & Joy

episodes.synopsis: As tensions with Philip increase, Elizabeth spends time with her old friend Porchey. Churchill’s portrait is painted for his 80th birthday.
episodes.title: Assassins

episodes.synopsis: Margaret and Peter are reunited, but another obstacle stands in their way. Elizabeth is torn between her duty as Queen and her love for her sister.
episodes.title: Gloriana

episodes.synopsis: As Philip leaves for a long tour, Elizabeth makes an upsetting discovery. Prime Minister Eden wants to strike back after Egypt seizes the Suez Canal.
episodes.title: Misadventure

episodes.synopsis: Elizabeth feels disconnected from Philip. Eden copes with international pressure and ill health. An interview stirs up harrowing memories for Philip.
episodes.title: A Company of Men

episodes.synopsis: Palace insiders try to prevent a scandal that could reflect poorly on Philip. Eden faces censure from his cabinet and the press.
episodes.title: Lisbon

episodes.synopsis: When Elizabeth and Philip throw a grand party for their 10th anniversary, both Margaret and the new Prime Minister experience romantic tribulations.
episodes.title: Beryl

episodes.synopsis: After Elizabeth makes a tone-deaf speech at a Jaguar factory, she and the monarchy come under public attack from an outspoken lord.
episodes.title: Marionettes

episodes.synopsis: A secret World War II document opens Elizabeth's eyes to grim realities about a family member. The Duke of Windsor campaigns to re-enter public life.
episodes.title: Vergangenheit

episodes.synopsis: A letter from Peter Townsend spurs Margaret to make a bold proposal. Elizabeth has good news that causes complications for Margaret.
episodes.title: Matrimonium

episodes.synopsis: Inspired by Jackie Kennedy and against her government's wishes, Elizabeth takes an unconventional approach to resolving an issue with Ghana.
episodes.title: Dear Mrs. Kennedy

episodes.synopsis: Philip insists that Prince Charles attend his alma mater in Scotland and reminisces about the life-changing difficulties he experienced there.
episodes.title: Paterfamilias

episodes.synopsis: A salacious government scandal hits close to home for Elizabeth and Philip. Elizabeth retreats to Scotland for rest during a difficult pregnancy.
episodes.title: Mystery Man

episodes.synopsis: Elizabeth grows concerned as Labour Party leader Harold Wilson becomes prime minister amid anti-monarchy sentiment and rumors of his possible KGB ties.
episodes.title: Olding

episodes.synopsis: With Britain in need of a financial bailout from the U.S., Elizabeth reluctantly enlists Margaret to assist in winning over President Johnson.
episodes.title: Margaretology

episodes.synopsis: Following a tragic accident at a Welsh mining village that quickly becomes political, both Elizabeth and Wilson struggle with their responses.
episodes.title: Aberfan

episodes.synopsis: As the royal family makes a documentary to boost their image, an unexpected guest arrives from Greece, throwing a wrench into Philip’s publicity plans.
episodes.title: Bubbikins

episodes.synopsis: Pursuing improvements in her racehorse management, Elizabeth imagines the life she might have had. Meanwhile, a plot against her government is brewing.
episodes.title: Coup

episodes.synopsis: Amid rising Welsh nationalism in the run-up to his investiture as Prince of Wales, Charles is sent to spend a semester there and learn the language.
episodes.title: Tywysog Cymru

episodes.synopsis: As the first men land on the moon, middle-aged Philip feels dissatisfied by his lack of achievement and begins searching for inspiration.
episodes.title: Moondust

episodes.synopsis: As Charles begins dating Camilla Shand, Elizabeth considers visiting an ill Duke of Windsor in Paris, whose destiny changed when he met Wallis Simpson.
episodes.title: Dangling Man

episodes.synopsis: While a government stalemate with mineworkers leads to nationwide power cuts, Charles's family intervenes in his deepening relationship with Camilla.
episodes.title: Imbroglio

episodes.synopsis: As her marriage disintegrates, Margaret seeks comfort elsewhere. But her fragile state of mind and lack of family support make true happiness elusive.
episodes.title: Cri de Coeur

episodes.synopsis: As Elizabeth welcomes Britain's first woman prime minister and Charles meets a young Diana Spencer, an IRA attack brings tragedy to the royal family.
episodes.title: Gold Stick

episodes.synopsis: Margaret Thatcher visits Balmoral but has trouble fitting in with the royal family, while Charles finds himself torn between his heart and family duty.
episodes.title: The Balmoral Test

episodes.synopsis: After Charles proposes, Diana moves into Buckingham Palace and finds her life filled with princess training, loneliness — and Camilla Parker Bowles.
episodes.title: Fairytale

episodes.synopsis: While Margaret Thatcher struggles with the disappearance of her favorite child, Elizabeth reexamines her relationships with her four children.
episodes.title: Favourites

episodes.synopsis: As Thatcher's policies create rising unemployment, a desperate man breaks into the palace, where he finds Elizabeth's bedroom and awakens her for a talk.
episodes.title: Fagan

episodes.synopsis: On a tour of Australia, Diana struggles to balance motherhood with her royal duties while both she and Charles cope with their marriage difficulties.
episodes.title: Terra Nullius

episodes.synopsis: Grappling with mental health issues, Margaret seeks help and discovers an appalling secret about estranged relatives of the royal family.
episodes.title: The Hereditary Principle

episodes.synopsis: As many nations condemn apartheid in South Africa, tension mounts between Thatcher and Elizabeth over their clashing opinions on applying sanctions.
Charles is caught in a deadly avalanche, prompting both him and Diana to reevaluate their commitment to their troubled marriage.
episodes.title: Avalanche

episodes.synopsis: Amid a growing challenge to her power, Thatcher fights for her position. Charles grows more determined to separate from Diana as their marriage unravels.
episodes.title: War
